'''Bill Murphy''' is a former [[United States|American]] professional [[wide receiver]] who played one season in 1969 for the [[New England Patriots]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://archive.patriots.com/alumni/index.cfm?ac=alumnibiosdetail&bio=12509|title=Official Website of the New England Patriots|date=2014-12-18|work=New England Patriots|access-date=2017-04-11}}</ref> He subsequently became a financial commentator and [[gold bug]], who serves as the chairman and director of the Gold Anti-Trust Action Committee. He graduated from [[Cornell University]] in 1968.
