{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{Infobox newspaper | name = Georgia Today | logo = Georgia Today Logo.jpg | image = Issue 790.jpg | caption = The front page for 5 November 2015. | type = Twice a week | format = | generalmanager = George Sharashidze<ref name=aus/> | founder = | publisher = [[Georgia Today Group]] | editor = | chiefeditor = Katie Ruth Davies<ref name=aus >{{cite web|url=http://georgiatoday.ge/en/285/|title=About Us|work=Georgia Today|accessdate=28 July 2015}}</ref> | maneditor = | newseditor = | managingeditordesign = | campuseditor = | campuschief = | opeditor = | sportseditor = | photoeditor = | staff = | foundation = {{start date and age|2000}} | political = | language = [[English language|English]] | ceased publication = | headquarters = [[Tbilisi]] | circulation = | sister newspapers = | ISSN = | oclc = | website = [http://www.georgiatoday.ge/ ''Georgia Today''] }} '''''Georgia Today''''' is an [[English language]] newspaper published in [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Georgia Profile|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/europe/country_profiles/1102477.stm#media|accessdate=10 October 2013|work=BBC}}</ref> The paper is published twice a week in two different versions - ''Georgia Today'' and ''Georgia Today Business''.<ref name=qua>{{cite news|title=Georgia Today ReBranded: Quality Designed with our Readers in Mind!|url=http://georgiatoday.ge/news/1810/Georgia-Today-ReBranded%3A-Quality-Designed-with-our-Readers-in-Mind%21|work=Georgia Today}}</ref>
==History and profile== ''Georgia Today'' was launched in 2000.<ref name=aus/> The paper, headquartered in [[Tbilisi]], is distributed both nationally and internationally.<ref>{{cite web|title=Newspaper Georgia Today|url=https://foursquare.com/v/newspaper-georgia-today/50b5b50fe4b0394bd20a03f4|work=Foursquare Labs|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Georgia|url=http://www.worldpress.org/newspapers/EUROPE/Georgia.cfm|work=Worldpress|accessdate=10 October 2013}}</ref>
In November 2015 the newspaper underwent a re-branding. With the consultation and major design input of awarding winning (European Newspaper of the Year 2015) newspaper designer Kevin Loftus,<ref>{{cite news|title=Introducing the Man behind the New Georgia Today|url=http://georgiatoday.ge/news/1816/Introducing-the-Man-behind-the-New-Georgia-Today|work=Georgia Today}}</ref> the layout of ''Georgia Today'' was redesigned and a new logo was created. Thereafter, it is published twice a week in two different versions - ''Georgia Today'', with articles on politics, society and culture, and ''GT Business'' which focuses on business, economy and law.<ref name=qua/> As of 29 December 2015, [[Georgian Journal]] was merged with Georgia Today.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://georgiatoday.ge/news/2519/New-Year-Brings-a-Welcome-Merger%E2%80%A6and-the-Expectation-of-More-to-Come|title=New Year Brings a Welcome Merger…and the Expectation of More to Come|author=|work=Georgia Today|date=29 December 2015|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref>
==Georgia Today Education== On 26 February 2016 Georgia Today Group announced the release of another version of ''GT - Georgia Today Education''. The paper is issued monthly and is mostly focused on education, technology, innovative business, international events and language learning. The main target audience of ''Georgia Today Education'' are teenagers and university students.<ref>{{cite news|title=Read. Learn. Enjoy. Introducing Georgia Today/Education|url=http://georgiatoday.ge/news/3085/Read.-Learn.-Enjoy.-Introducing-Georgia-Today-Education|work=Georgia Today}}</ref>
