'''Peter Thal Larsen''' is a [[Netherlands|Dutch]] journalist.<ref name="Deloitte">{{cite web|url=http://www.deloitte.com/view/en_LU/lu/lu-events/horizon-conference-2012/e58825c60b1a7310VgnVCM3000001c56f00aRCRD.htm|title=Mr. Peter Thal Larsen, Former FT banking editor, Breakingviews|publisher=Deloitte|year=2012|accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>
Thal Larsen graduated from [[Bristol University]] before going on to the [[London School of Economics]].<ref name="Deloitte"/> He began working for the ''[[Financial Times]]'' in 1999 and moved to the paper's [[New York City]] office the following year, first as a financial correspondent and then U.S. communications editor. He returned to [[London]] in 2004 to become banking editor, leading the paper's coverage of the financial crisis and the [[2008 United Kingdom bank rescue package]].<ref name="Guardian20090415"/> In 2009, he departed to become [[Reuters]]' European comment editor, reporting to Jonathan Ford.<ref name="Guardian20090415">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2009/apr/15/peter-thal-larsen-financial-times-reuters|first=Oliver|last=Luft|title=Peter Thal Larsen quits Financial Times for Reuters|work=The Guardian|date=2009-04-15|accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref> Following Reuters' acquisition of [[Breakingviews]] later that year he became assistant editor of Reuters Breakingviews. In 2012, he moved to [[Hong Kong]] to take up a new position within Reuters as the Asia editor for Breakingviews.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.talkingbiznews.com/1/reuters-breakingviews-names-asia-editor/|first=Chris|last=Roush|title=Reuters Breakingviews names Asia editor|work=Talking Biz News|date=2012-06-18|accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>
Thal Larsen was one of a number of senior financial journalists who reported on the effects of the financial crisis on [[The Royal Bank of Scotland]], and was interviewed by [[Ian Fraser (broadcaster)|Ian Fraser]] for a 2011 [[BBC Two]] documentary on the topic.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ianfraser.org/rbs-inside-the-bank-that-ran-out-of-money-2/|title=Inside the Royal Bank of Scotland|publisher=ianfraser.org|date=2011-11-21|accessdate=2013-04-20}}</ref>
