A '''stripped book''' is a [[mass market paperback]] that has been stripped of its cover in order to be [[Pulping|pulped]] and [[Paper recycling|recycled]] as a result of lack of sales. The covers are returned to the publisher as evidence that the books have been destroyed and the books are discarded or recycled into paper or cardboard products. However, some stripped books end up back on the marketplace, and are sold at places like [[flea markets]].
